            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle in your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> with 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until all the water has absorbed, the rice is cooked and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1680107601336-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1680107601336-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1680107601336-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1680107601336-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1680107601336-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, remove the dish from the oven and set aside for 5 min to steam (keep the lid on!) – this is your <strong>oven-baked chicken breast biryani</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> green chilli[es] </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1680107604781-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1680107604781-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1680107604781-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1680107604781-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1680107604781-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, fluff the<strong> oven-baked chicken breast biryani </strong>with a fork and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Top with a dollop of<strong> natural yoghurt</strong>, the <strong>sliced green chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> crispy onions</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for the cardamom pods and bay leaves and discard!</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
